---
// HOME Beat 2 — what Andon does. Heading + body + standalone link, left on rail.
const ARROW = `<path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"/>`;
---

<section class="px-6 py-8 md:px-10 md:py-12">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[72rem]">
    <h2
      class="rise max-w-[42rem] text-balance font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink md:text-[2.5rem]"
    >
      Andon measures the supply, while the cell is making protein.
    </h2>
    <p
      class="rise mt-6 max-w-[46rem] text-lg leading-[1.75] text-muted"
      style="animation-delay: 100ms"
    >
      We read that supply state directly, in the systems proteins are actually
      made in, from microbes to mammalian cells. It answers both questions that
      matter: whether a sequence will express, and how much you'll get.
    </p>
    <a
      href="/science"
      class="rise mt-7 inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-button text-sm tracking-wide text-accent-700 transition-colors hover:text-accent-800"
      style="animation-delay: 180ms"
    >
      The science
      <svg
        width="16"
        height="16"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        aria-hidden="true"
        set:html={ARROW}
      />
    </a>
  </div>
</section>
